quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  13,43,"The infidels, moreover, will say; Thou art not sent of God. SAY: God is witness enough betwixt me and you, and, whoever hath knowledge of the Book"
  14,1,"ELIF. LAM. RA. This Book have we sent down to thee that by their Lord's permission thou mayest bring men out of darkness into light, into the path of the Mighty, the Glorious"
  14,2,"Of God; to whom belongeth whatever is in the Heavens and whatever is on the Earth: and woe! for their terrible punishment, to the infidels"
  14,3,"Who love the life that now is, above that which is to come, and mislead from the way of God, and seek to make it crooked. These are in a far-gone error"
  14,4,"And in order that He might speak plainly to them, we have not sent any Apostle, save with the speech of his own people; but God misleadeth whom He will, and whom He will he guideth: and He is the Mighty, the Wise"
  14,5,"Of old did we send Moses with our signs: and said to him, \"Bring forth thy people from the darkness into the light, and remind them of the days of God.\" Verily, in this are signs for every patient, grateful person"